,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127582201,"data":"  TASK: Alternating-position glyph substitution over base-3 digit strings with unknown endianness; witness glyph↔digit pairs fix a unique hidden isomorphism; MAP probes return mismatch mass; commit with DIGITS. RL subskill: hypothesis formation + planning under constraint.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127589488,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127593686,"data":"[USER — Turn 1]\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127598359,"data":"A fixed secret turns each nonnegative integer into a **glyph string** over ['⬡', '⬢', '⬣'].\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127603494,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127607838,"data":"Structure (constant for this episode, all unknown):\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127612254,"data":"- Base-three expansion with **no leading-zero digit** except the integer 0.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127616946,"data":"- The digit list is read either **most-significant-first** or **reversed** along the string.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127621471,"data":"- Glyph at index 0 of that list uses one digit→glyph bijection; index 1 uses another **independent** bijection on the same three glyphs; indices alternate.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127626161,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127630198,"data":"**Witness rows** (each row: glyph string, then the matching digit list in MSB-first standard form using characters 0, 1, 2 only):\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.12763487,"data":"- `⬣⬢⬢⬣⬢⬢`  →  `100100`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.12763981,"data":"- `⬡⬣⬡⬣⬣`  →  `21211`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127644637,"data":"- `⬣⬡⬡⬡⬢`  →  `12220`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127649231,"data":"- `⬣⬢⬢⬢⬣⬡`  →  `100012`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127653799,"data":"- `⬡⬢⬡⬡⬣`  →  `20221`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.12765839,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127662551,"data":"**Test glyph string:** `⬣⬣⬢⬡⬣`\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127667186,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127671348,"data":"Reply each turn with **one** line:\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127676116,"data":"- Probe: `MAP EVEN abc ODD def ENDIAN MSB` or `... ENDIAN LSB` where `abc` and `def` are each a permutation of 012 meaning, in glyph order ['⬡', '⬢', '⬣'], the digit carried by ⬡, ⬢, ⬣ at even and odd indices respectively.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127682035,"data":"- Final answer: `DIGITS zzz...` — MSB-first 0/1/2 digit list for the test string under the episode rules.\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127687209,"data":"\n"}
,{"stream_name":"stdout","time":46.127691662,"data":"After a `MAP` line you receive the **total digit mismatches** summed across all witness rows (exact Hamming; length mismatch counts per position). 0 means the probe matches every witness.\n"}
